The paper focuses on object proposal methods in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves analyzing the impact of various object-level characteristics on the performance of existing methods, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The study also involves analyzing the localization accuracy and latency of object proposal methods, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
